name: Starman
desc: SpaceX launched a Tesla with a mannequin astronaut called Starman into space.

name: Giant Disco Ball
desc: American aerospace company Rocket Lab sent a giant disco ball called the Humanity Star into space. It was 3 feet in diameter and featured 65 reflective panels.

name: Big Mac
desc: As part of a promotional stunt for McDelivery, McDonald's Big Mac and fries were sent to the edge of space aboard a weather balloon. The meal was safely brought back to Earth after the balloon burst.

name: Lego Man
desc: Two teenagers from Toronto, Canada, launched a 'Lego Man in Space' using a helium-filled weather balloon and captured breathtaking video footage of the miniature toy figure.

name: Running Shoes
desc: The YouTube channel The Running Channel partnered with Brooks to send a pair of running shoes into Stratosphere

name: KitKat
desc: In 2012, Kit Kat launched a campaign called 'Goes To Space! #BreakFromGravity' to support Felix Baumgartner's record-breaking skydive

name: Slice of Pizza and book
desc: YouTuber Nick DiGiovanni sent a slice of pizza and his book, Knife Drop, into space, tethered to a balloon

name: Kermit The Frog
desc: In 2023, Kermit the Frog was sent into space aboard a high-altitude weather balloon
